page.title: 03General Review
page.content: During the day wildlife can be seen on the fields e.g. rabbits,hares,wild ducks,moorhens,partridges and pheasants. The area is criss-crossed by many tracks,some of which are maintained by the Board,others by farmers themselves being infilled with rubble from demolished farmhouses. In the village of Keadby the housing consists mainly of terraces or semi-detached.Most of the residents work elsewhere. Many anglers visit the village during the coarse fishing season and although there were pollution problems some years ago,good catches of roach,bream,perch and eels can be had from the canal and the three drains, and angling matches are regularly held.
